-- Staff for South Africa's PIC Can't Claim Board Fees, Business Report Says
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-07-05T06:12:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/staff-for-south-africa-s-pic-can-t-claim-board-fees-business-report-says.html

          
          
             Employees of the Public Investment
Corp., which manages 800 billion rand ($103 billion) in South
African government pensions, have no claim on fees they may earn
as directors of companies that the PIC is invested in,  Business
Report  said, citing a court judgment.  
 Fees paid to employees of the PIC are the property of the
pension fund it manages and not of the individuals, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper reported, citing a judge it didnâ€™t
identify. The case referred to former PIC employee Kagiso
Bodigelo who wanted to keep 2.3 million rand ($298,000) in
director fees from four companies.  
